snippet.textDisplay:
He's claiming this virus is 10-20 times more lethal than the flu but those numbers have to be drastically skewed. How couldn't they be? The amount of confirmed corona virus cases is tiny compared to the seasonal flu. There's millions of cases of the flu each year in the USA alone. There's less than 2000 confirmed cases of the corona virus in the USA as of this moment and the vast majority of deaths have occurred in elderly at-risk individuals. The sample size is microscopic compared to the flu. As testing increases, as the confirmed cases rize, the mortality rate will go down. With such a small sample size, each death has a much larger effect on the overall mortality percentage. I'm just talking the simple math of it. Not which is more deadly.

As testing increases, more cases will be confirmed, and thus the percentage of deaths will decrease and that brings the mortality rate down.

snippet.textDisplay:
If you wanted to get yourself tested for the coronavirus, depending on where you live in this country, it would cost you between $1500-$3000. The average American does not have thousands of dollars lying around to see if they may or may not have an illness. And that’s only to see if you have it. To treat it, it would cost between $5000-$10,000. Because of this, Americans are going to avoid going to get checked which would lead to the virus spreading more due to the fact that they don’t know they have it.

In Australia, where they have a Medicare for all system, just how they do in Israel & the UK & Canada, and every other advanced country on Earth, it’s free to test and treat, which would lead to more people checking if they have it and if they do, are far less likely to spread it by quarantining themselves and getting the proper treatment.
The coronavirus is the perfect reason why we desperately need a Medicare for all system, and this so called “CNN Doctor” who did not bring up a need for a Medicare for all system is a corporatist joke.
Shame on Ernie Johnson, the multi millionaire who’s content with the status quo for advising us to watch CNN, who is extremely pro corporate and anti-Medicare for all, and props to Kenny’s ignorance who thinks the average American can fork out thousands of dollars to see if they have it. Typical millionaires who are so out of touch with the working people of this country, especially Shaq who admitted to voting for Trump simply to keep his taxes lower. Clearly you need help paying your bills (sarcasm).

snippet.textDisplay: The images from elseware show the testing is a two step...first they poke one if those fancy thermometers at your forehead as one enters or leaves a venue, and the examiners are in full gear...from failing this first step, I imagine one is taken aside and given the virus test...if that is positive, one is quarentined...hereabout, I'm not seeing in the news the geared up temperature test, or first hand reports of what happened to those positive for the virus, and I listen for this...back from overseas, patients go to military bases...I hear nothing about hospital wings or wards or even new hospitals set aside, as looks to be the case in China...Charles is waiting for test result in his condo...where might be Tom Hanks and his wife?...this 'where do we go if we have this?' question doesnt get asked, and 'where do we go if we think we have this? problematic...St. Joseph is saying (my provider), stay home if you have a cold/flu...this to limit spread...but they are very vague on how to get care over the phone, or internet...speaking of which, I cant find any crowd source forums chatting up, like I can for my dog's health...and a singular one time test isnt enough...we should check our temps everyday, and everyday we should be able to avail ourselves of the geared up virus testors...it's not so different from the inspection set up for passengers at airports?...the problem, I mean...I dunno...this is a good report, sure, but how this is affecting everday folk is lost, and like most things obfusicated in the yt comment sections by trolls, which is too bad, as the comment sections a good place to sort ideas, which, I have it, all have to be vetted by Pence and the White House...😕
